<div id="review_457958095" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/457958095" />
    <a title="Ruth" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/335159-ruth"><img alt="Ruth" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1491245404p2/335159.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/457958095?book_show_action=true">Nov 17, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ruth" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ruth" href="/user/show/335159-ruth">Ruth</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer457958095" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2548857205503623314">Because I loved Jon Clinch’s <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/102077.Finn' title='Finn by Jon Clinch' rel='nofollow noopener'>Finn</a> and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7493646.Kings_of_the_Earth' title='Kings of the Earth by Jon Clinch' rel='nofollow noopener'>Kings of the Earth</a> so much I could hardly wait to get my hands on The Thief of Auschwitz. Unfortunately, Clinch set the jump pretty high for himself with the first two books, so that I couldn’t help feeling a little disappointed in this one. Perhaps it’s because so many books have been written about the Holocaust, or perhaps it’s because I’ve read way too many. This is a well-written book that I plowed right through. But…but… Don’t get me wrong, it’s an exce</span>
  <span id="freeText2548857205503623314" style="display:none">Because I loved Jon Clinch’s <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/102077.Finn" title="Finn by Jon Clinch" rel="nofollow noopener">Finn</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7493646.Kings_of_the_Earth" title="Kings of the Earth by Jon Clinch" rel="nofollow noopener">Kings of the Earth</a> so much I could hardly wait to get my hands on The Thief of Auschwitz. Unfortunately, Clinch set the jump pretty high for himself with the first two books, so that I couldn’t help feeling a little disappointed in this one. Perhaps it’s because so many books have been written about the Holocaust, or perhaps it’s because I’ve read way too many. This is a well-written book that I plowed right through. But…but… Don’t get me wrong, it’s an excellent book, but I expected something exceptional, and this wasn’t. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2548857205503623314" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


