<div id="review_555142242" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/555142242" />
    <a title="Cindy S" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1392138-cindy-s"><img alt="Cindy S" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1219534110p2/1392138.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/555142242?book_show_action=true">Mar 07, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cindy S" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cindy S" href="/user/show/1392138-cindy-s">Cindy S</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer555142242" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5863044270362873069">This is the inspirational, heartbreaking story of the Rosen family, Jacob, Eidel, Max and Lydia, caught in the Nazi takeover. Jacob is a barber and Eidel is an artist. Both skills are utilized in the concentration camp. The story alternates with a narrative by Max as an old man, living in America. Moving and horrifying, it is a story of unbelievable courage and the need to remain human while enduring extreme brutality. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

