<div id="review_1035558882" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1035558882" />
    <a title="Sara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/554760-sara"><img alt="Sara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1250006215p2/554760.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1035558882?book_show_action=true">Aug 24, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sara" href="/user/show/554760-sara">Sara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/554760-sara?shelf=2014-reads">2014-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1035558882" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16454629247007663435">I can&apos;t put my finger on why I didn&apos;t love this book, but I didn&apos;t. For such an emotional subject matter, I never felt any true emotion in the characters. They all seemed flat and I had trouble caring about them (even though they were in such a horrible setting). Maybe it was the writing style that I had trouble with, but whatever it was, I didn&apos;t enjoy this book.</span>
  <span id="freeText16454629247007663435" style="display:none">I can't put my finger on why I didn't love this book, but I didn't. For such an emotional subject matter, I never felt any true emotion in the characters. They all seemed flat and I had trouble caring about them (even though they were in such a horrible setting). Maybe it was the writing style that I had trouble with, but whatever it was, I didn't enjoy this book.</span>
